                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>THOMAS WHITE. I am a <rs id="t18250915-322-viclabel1738" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-322-victim1617 t18250915-322-viclabel1738"></join>. I know the prisoner - he was a <rs id="t18250915-322-deflabel1739" type="occupation">seaman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-322-defend1616 t18250915-322-deflabel1739"></join> - he frequently visited me; he came on the 1st of August, but I was not at home; the next morning there was a silver table-spoon missing - it had been used on the Sunday, and was in the dishes - he had dined with us on the Sunday - and invited himself to dine on the Monday.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Can you swear I came there on Monday to dinner? A. Yes.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-322-person1618">
                  METCALF 
                  HOPGOOD
               <interp inst="t18250915-322-person1618" type="surname" value="HOPGOOD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-322-person1618" type="given" value="METCALF"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-322-person1618" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a silver-smith, and live in Bishopsgate-street. The prisoner brought this spoon to me, on Monday, the 1st of August, between three and four o'clock, for sale.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-322-person1619">
                  JOHN 
                  GREEN
               <interp inst="t18250915-322-person1619" type="surname" value="GREEN"></interp>
